<span class="displaytext"><h3>"only one" ad highlights (candidate last)'s diplomatic experience</h3>santa fe, nm-- the presidential campaign of new mexico governor (candidate full) today released an ad touting (candidate last)'s one of a kind experience as a diplomatic troubleshooter around the world.<p>the ad, entitled "only one," details a hostage situation in iraq that then-congressman (candidate last) was called upon to defuse. in the 60-second spot, bill barloon, the late david daliberti, and his wife kathy daliberti praise (candidate last) for obtaining the release of the two men from iraqi leader saddam hussein in july 1995. </p><p>see the ad and background materials at:<br/><a href="http://action.(candidate last)forpresident.com/onlyone">http://action.(candidate last)forpresident.com/onlyone</a> </p><p>"governor (candidate last) is the only candidate with hands-on experience in tense international disputes," campaign manager dave contarino said. "this year, governor (candidate last) has helped shut down north korea's largest nuclear reactor and has obtained a temporary cease-fire in darfur. (candidate full)'s record speaks for itself: even in the most hostile situations, he gets the job done right. the united states no longer can afford on-the-job diplomatic training and needs a president with the kind of international experience that only (candidate full) has." </p><p>the ad is the latest in a series of spots that have spread governor (candidate last)'s message to voters around the country. (candidate last) steadily has climbed in the polls in the early caucus state of iowa and early primary state of new hampshire. governor (candidate last) registers double-digit support in both the recent arg iowa and rasmussen new hampshire polls.</p></span>



